[5] Cholera, diarrhea - Sierra Leone (Bonthe)
Date: Fri 9 Dec 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and Concord Times (Freetown) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200512090591.html>

Cholera kills 18 children in Bonthe
-----------------------------------
18 children are reported to have died of diarrhea in fishing villages
around Delken and its surrounding area in the Bonthe district, southern
Sierra Leone over the past week. This epidemic is reported to have affected
over 1000 people, of whom 30 are children, in that area.
An emergency medical response team from the Ministry of Health and
Sanitation and World Vision-Sierra Leone has been dispatched to the area to
carry out curative and preventive treatment.
Elizabeth Domboi, nurse in charge of health and sanitation, confirmed that
the epidemic killed 18 children before native herbalists put it under
control. She complained that local residents in the district have negative
response towards conventional treatment.
It should be noted that 10 years ago, an outbreak of diarrhea and cholera
claimed the lives of more than 50 people in villages around Bonthe and part
of neighboring Moyamba district
[byline: Tanu Jalloh]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Although the posting's title refers to cholera, the story itself mentions
diarrhea only. The mortality in the outbreak certainly suggests _V.
cholerae_ infection. - Mod. LL]
